Kotak cherry devops project  Steps followed 



Step 1) Created ec2 instance to host git local repository, Terraform, Docker and kubernetes and helm. (warning ec2 instance is on public ip)
Step 2) pushed  node js code from git to github
step 3) created docker image of my node js code as kotak-cherry-app
step 4) brought container up  and mapped to port 8080 of ec2 instance to container
step 5) could access the kotak-cherry-app cotainer from public ip of ec2 instance 
step 5) Then did setup of eks using terrform by creating terraform files
step 6) i have created eks cluster successfully but there is error in bringing pods up 
step 7) I have done port  mapping with ec2 and   docker container on port 8080 where application is running.
